      <item>
        <title>CarDash</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/resources/cardash.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CarDash is my second published Android game. It has been developed in four days, including graphics and Audio. I made this game because in Teesside University I have a subject of Mobile programming and I decided to do a complete game as final project. The objectives were that the game should have three kind of inputs, I decided to use the GPS to change the sprites/graphics and the direction of driving (if you are in UK for example), The touch screen to navigate between menu and to switch between roads, and the accelerometer to increase or decrease the car speed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CarDash has been developed using the framework Cocos2d-x 3.10v and C++&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can download it for free here:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.JAPR.CarDash&quot;&gt;https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.JAPR.CarDash&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enjoy it!&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
